        "authorId" : "a66b5f61-1206-4ddd-b280-befb0005276f",
        "body" : "Could you please use `target_link_libraries()` when setting include directories like this? I would like to make it explicit that it's `PUBLIC` or `PRIVATE` so that the conversion to imported targets later is easier. Also, this might be broken if we have builtin_gsl=ON, for the same reason that `net/netxng` was. The include directory will point to the build directory and make CMake error out. This is probably one of the cases where we will have to wait before fully converting to the new style. Also, keep an eye for failures in dictionaries as for FFTW. If dictionary generation fails, we need to add `DICTIONARY_OPTIONS` with the GSL include directory.",
